I"˚<p>As a part of OSINT/Recon activity to identify sensitive information for specific organisation/website most of the security engineers were using Google dorks. In this article we were identifying the vulnerable websites which exposes .git folders in their web servers.</p>

<h5 id="google-dork---git-folder-exposure">Google Dork - .git folder exposure:</h5>

<figure>
<img src="/redteam-git-config-googledork/gdrkgit.png" alt="Google dork" />
<figcaption> git folder google dork </figcaption>
</figure>

<h4 id="google-dork">Google Dork:</h4>
<div class="language-text highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>intext:"index of /.git" "parent directory"
</code></pre></div></div>
<h4 id="defend-git-folder-exposed-web-servers">Defend .git folder exposed Web servers:</h4>
<pre><code class="language-cfg">&lt;Directory ~ ‚Äú\.git‚Äù&gt;
Order deny,allow
Deny from all
&lt;/Directory&gt;
</code></pre>

